&lt;li&gt;Sanitary sewer systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Storm drain systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Concrete improvements (curb, gutter, sidewalks, structures)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Roadway and transportation projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify construction complies with plans, specifications, and agency standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare daily inspection reports documenting progress, quantities, and issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with contractors, engineers, and public agency representatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor material quality, installation methods, and workmanship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify deficiencies and ensure corrective actions are completed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project meetings and provide field input.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with safety standards and job-site requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of construction activities and testing results.&lt;/li&gt;
